properties.Name: AminoAcidDerivative
properties.Description:
An amino acid derivative is a molecule that is generated using an amino acid as a starting point (precursor).

Ex:
5-HTP (5-hydroxytryptophan)

Columns.Name: AminoAcidDerivativeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an amino acid derivative.

Columns.Name: AminoAcidDerivativeName
Columns.Description:
The name of an amino acid.

Ex:
5-HTP (5-hydroxytryptophan)

Columns.Name: AminoAcidDerivativeNotation
Columns.Description:
The notation of an amino acid.

Ex:
5-HTP (5-hydroxytryptophan)

Columns.Name: AminoAcidId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an amino acid.
